Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bujumbura, 7 Feb (ABP-BUR/PANA) -- Mr. Anatole 
Kanyenkiko [a Tutsi with a Hutu mother, married to a Rwandan 
Hutu] has been appointed prime minister by the head of state of 
Burundi, Cyprien Ntaryamira, to replace Mrs. Sylvie Kinigi, a 
communique issued Monday [7 February] in Bujumbura said. 
  The new Burundian head of government was formerly the 
minister of public works and equipment. 

